Contributing to DIET_APP
Thank you for your interest in contributing! To maintain a high standard of code and a smooth workflow, please follow these steps.

1. 🔍 Find an Issue or Suggest an Idea
Check the Issues tab to find existing tasks or bugs.

If you have a new idea, open a New Issue to discuss it before starting work. This ensures your efforts align with the project's goals.

2. 🍴 Fork and Clone
Fork this repository to your own GitHub account.

Clone your fork to your local machine:

Bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/DIET_APP.git
Add the original repository as an upstream remote to stay updated:

Bash
git remote add upstream https://github.com/harinarayana1457-cmyk/DIET_APP.git
3. 🌿 Create a Branch
Always create a new branch for your changes. Use a descriptive name:

Bash
git checkout -b feature/your-feature-name
# OR
git checkout -b fix/bug-name
4. 🛠 Make Your Changes
Code Style: Follow the existing "terminal-brutalist" dark-mode aesthetic.

Linting: Ensure your code is clean and follows React.js best practices.

Testing: Run the app locally to verify that your changes don't break existing functionality.

5. 💾 Commit and Push
Stage your changes:

Bash
git add .
Commit with a clear, concise message:

Bash
git commit -m "feat: add macro-nutrient progress bar"
Push to your fork:

Bash
git push origin feature/your-feature-name
6. 🚀 Open a Pull Request (PR)
Go to the original DIET_APP repository on GitHub.

Click Compare & pull request.

Provide a clear description of your changes and reference any related issues (e.g., Closes #12).

Wait for a review. Be open to feedback and making adjustments if requested!

⚖️ Community Standards
Be respectful and constructive in all communications.

Focus on keeping the UI clutter-free and performant.

Happy Coding!
